{
	"$comment": "OpenShutter template kit — Studio. v0.1 spike: theme + Home page only. Installer maps `pages[]` into MongoDB `pages` rows and module entries into `page_modules`, and `theme` into the matching `themes` row + `site_config.template` defaults. Aliases use the pack prefix `s-` so they coexist with default unprefixed pages used as fallback (per TEMPLATING.md §4 alias resolution).",

	"$comment_packaging": "IMPORTANT — this JSON file is DATA ONLY. It does NOT carry the SCSS or any module/component source. A complete 'template package' is THREE things shipped together, with parts 1 and 3 co-located under frontend/src/templates/<packId>/ so the pack can be migrated as one folder: (1) the pack's SCSS + Svelte under frontend/src/templates/<packId>/ (e.g. styles/_hero.scss, styles/_layoutShell.scss, styles/_cta.scss, plus any pack-specific module overrides registered via TEMPLATE_PAGE_BUILDER_OVERRIDES); (2) any NEW page-builder modules referenced in `newModules` below (e.g. heroStats, personBio, contactInfo) implemented under frontend/src/lib/page-builder/modules/<Name>/ and registered in PageRenderer.svelte's baseModuleMap — these live with the page-builder, not the pack, since they're reusable across packs; (3) this JSON file (frontend/src/templates/<packId>/<packId>.kit.json), fed to backend/src/scripts/install-template-kit.ts to write pages/page_modules/site_config. Workflow: code+SCSS must land in the frontend source tree and a frontend build/redeploy must run BEFORE the installer is invoked against a live DB — otherwise pages will reference classes/modules that don't exist in the deployed bundle. Future v0.2: decide between bundling SCSS as a runtime-loaded asset inside the kit, scaffolding pack files into the source tree from the installer, or restricting kits to base-CSS-only.",

